ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're looking at this section as an Architecture senior, you clearly have too much time on your hands. You gotta take it at this point.
A new way of looking at things you've been thinking about for three years. Enjoy it.
Learn a lot of new technical things in the last semester. Good final course.
Overall a great course in that it doesn't kill you but still really pushes you in all aspects of design. You actually understand what direction you are headed and can make work that reflects that.
